definitions.definition: A member of a confederacy of several southeastern Native American tribes , who inhabited much of what is now East Texas , western Louisiana and portions of southern Arkansas and Oklahoma in the 16th century.

main_definition: A member of a confederacy of several southeastern Native American tribes , who inhabited much of what is now East Texas , western Louisiana and portions of southern Arkansas and Oklahoma in the 16th century.

definitions.definition: A Caddoan language of the Southern Plains of the United States, spoken by the Caddo Nation of Oklahoma .

main_definition: A Caddoan language of the Southern Plains of the United States, spoken by the Caddo Nation of Oklahoma .
